<inglise> Article 25 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 25 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Bank shall at all times be entitled to transfer its assets in the currency of one Member State into the currency of another Member State in order to carry out financial operations corresponding to the task set out in Article 130 of this Treaty, taking into account the provisions of Article 23 of this Statute. </inglise>
